commit_message:
Fix incompatiblity issue in VNX manila driver

When running Manila with VNX File OE 8.1.6 or later,
if user creates a NFS share in Manila, driver will
report nas command error when setting nfs permission.

This fix will use updated nas command to resolve it.

Change-Id: I0550cdf01278fa4e9aeed7891152fed6dcc0eefc
Closes-Bug: #1465543
(cherry picked from commit 081f9226e46ba801ba7be8024aebb967aba7f2e9)

commit_message:
Fix no attribute 'is_dvr_router' error in test_l3_agent_scheduler

cls.is_dvr_router attribute is invalid in the case which result of the
is_extension_enabled() called in resource_setup() is false.
This patch fixes it.

Closes-bug: #1465623
Change-Id: If3e9f80991b2675b4700c7cdc80b5689b444d40b

cinder and neutron already switch to PyMySQL. glance will switch when oslo.db will use PyMySQL (so it depends on this change). nova is also blocked by this change. For glance and nova, the problem is that DB migration is no more tested!

To be clear: MySQL-python still works with the right connector URL, so applications can still use MySQL-Python even if we release a new version of oslo.db with this change.

Since most major OpenStack applications want PyMySQL, I don't see any reason to continue to support officially MySQL-python in oslo.db. We should just help remaining applications (ex: glance, nova) to switch to finish the switch before the release of OpenStack Liberty."}, {'account_id': 9107, 'date': '2015-06-17 22:23:38.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

Viktor, Roman: Are you ok with the latest patch?'}, {'account_id': 6849, 'date': '2015-06-18 09:00:49.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

I'm ok with changing the default driver to PyMySQL in oslo.db.

At the same time, choose of a particular driver is up to operators, IMO. If MySQL-Python suits them better, I see no reason why we should drop MySQL-Python support completely. I agree with Victor on that we should add an additional tox env to test MySQL-Python for py27, as well as we should keep the doc section on how to use it, if someone really needs that.

Having said that, I agree PyMySQL is a much better default, given the fact we use eventlet... So let's fix the unit tests and docs, add a tox env and merge this :)

P.S. this patch to oslo.db is not a blocker for any other project, they are free to use the notion of configurable URLs for tests - https://github.com/openstack/oslo.db/blob/master/oslo_db/sqlalchemy/provision.py#L288-L305"}, {'account_id': 7491, 'date': '2015-06-18 12:21:35.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 5.'}, {'account_id': 6849, 'date': '2015-06-18 12:40:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: Code-Review-1

commit_message:
Switch from MySQL-python to PyMySQL

As discussed in the Liberty Design Summit "Moving apps to Python 3"
cross-project workshop, the way forward in the near future is to
switch to the pure-python PyMySQL library as a default.

Added a special test environment to keep MySQL-python support.
Documentation modified.

https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/liberty-cross-project-python3

Change-Id: I12b32dc097a121bd43991bc38dd4d289b65e86c1

commit_message:
Pass token and endpoint to swift os_options

get_capabilities runs through a code path in swiftclient where the auth
token pieces need to be in os_options. We also need to tell swift to use
keystone auth, not swift auth.

Change-Id: I3768f40059b6f6591f67e47a3202ed17779d0fe8

[{'created': '2015-06-17 13:57:17.000000000', 'message': 'Add updates and security repositories

Added yum repositories for mos?.?-updates
and mos?.?-security, depending on Fuel version

After running fuelmenu, updates repo will be
verified that it can be resolved and download
updates. If updates fail or resolution fails,
a warning is displayed at the end of deployment
and broadcast to Fuel UI.

This point was selected because Internet access
is usually not available until after fuelmenu
has been run.

Change-Id: I30e8c854147bed9901470bf1a98875180d808ab4

and mos?.?-security, depending on Fuel version

verified that it can be resolved and accessible
via HTTP. If this fails, a warning is displayed
at the end of deployment and broadcast to Fuel UI.

is usually not available until after fuelmenu
has been run.

commit_message:
Add updates and security repositories

Added yum repositories for mos?.?-updates
and mos?.?-security, depending on Fuel version

After running fuelmenu, updates repo will be
verified that it can be resolved and accessible
via HTTP. If this fails, a warning is displayed
at the end of deployment and broadcast to Fuel UI.

This point was selected because Internet access
is usually not available until after fuelmenu
has been run.

Change-Id: I30e8c854147bed9901470bf1a98875180d808ab4
Partial-Bug: #1466080
Partial-Bug: #1466070

commit_message:
fuel_upgrade: setup update/security repos

In order to deliver bugfixes and improvements to customers we have to
setup our online repos in case of successful upgrade. These repos
have to be marked with "skip_if_available" flag so yum won't fall
if there's no connectivity to them (e.g. no Internet access).

Closes-Bug: #1466418

Change-Id: I6626ff5e92c53c487f69491c09c3e0bcf022d5d4
Signed-off-by: Igor Kalnitsky <igor@kalnitsky.org>

commit_message:
Enable Manila project in devstack hooks

All our CI Tempest jobs use 'plugin' approach of devstack that appeared
only in Kilo release. So, for the moment Manila is not even installed
and all Tempest tests are skipped because of it.

Change-Id: I45450ffdc472ad5d3f930b83b0d2288cf33975b8

commit_message:
puppet: make Puppet 4 unit test jobs voting

All Puppet OpenStack modules are Puppet4 compliant.
The jobs were not voting but since now all of our modules are ready, we
want to have the job voting so we keep the job stable and our code
Puppet 4 compliant.

It also makes sure it's not blocking stackforge/puppet-openstack-cloud
Puppet module, which is not part of Puppet OpenStack modules.

Change-Id: I961a64d5495b2126a25404e953c4681d40506c28

commit_message:
Fix stackforge repo refs in devstack/lib/mistral

Update two mentions to mistral's github repositories
in contrib/devstack/lib/mistral from stackforge to
their new place within the openstack user on github.

Change-Id: I1067a30f773ea6dd83bb8101309245cbc7a41e8a
Closes-Bug: 1466149

connection uri for MySQL.

Change-Id: I590d2b3707548a51eaab358a5a8a780b2ceffa02
'}]
commit_message:
Enable migration tests for MySQL

MySQL igration tests skipped with PyMySQL because of wrong default
connection uri - `mysql//...` instead of `mysql+pymysql://`. This patch
uses OS_TEST_DBAPI_ADMIN_CONNECTION evn variable to set correct
connection uri for MySQL.

Change-Id: I590d2b3707548a51eaab358a5a8a780b2ceffa02

commit_message:
Fix broken ACL tests

In keystonemiddleware 2.0.0 the token cache keys are sha256 hashes of the
token key. For versions of keystonemiddleware < 2.0.0 this is not the
case, so this patch is changing the FakeMemcache class to support both.

Change-Id: I14f6a47437ca861d3135bedbfe2b3a54de211182
Closes-Bug: #1466405

commit_message:
Add missing default policy rules for servers' actions

At this patch https://review.openstack.org/#/c/149931 adds new rules
for servers' actions. But those rules missed in
policy.d/00-os-compute-api.json. This patch adds them back.

Change-Id: I4942574e8bad3743430d0171ff0e3cab81cbc2ab
Closes-Bug: #1435390

commit_message:
Properly kill processes in namespaces on DHCP/L3 agent stop/start

get_pid_list_for_ns_list function uses namespaces list as an argument.
Variable $ns_list is a string of namespaces divided by spaces.
To properly use all of its values we need to use all arguments ($@).

Closes-bug: #1442251

Conflicts:
	deployment/puppet/cluster/files/ocf/neutron-agent-dhcp
	deployment/puppet/cluster/files/ocf/neutron-agent-l3

Change-Id: I32654bf7e537247f97070ed27ab8d7b4de5b35c7

commit_message:
Fix DHCP conditionals

Changed dhcp conditionals to utilize {{varname|bool}} instead
of attempting a boolean and string compare on them in case a setting
is explicitly stored as a string.

Change-Id: Iadf9d8fa1a20905afe0141acc23f9f880e6d4a84

commit_message:
Move sahara templates to stand alone module

Move sahara templates creation to stand alone module
sahara_templates due to syncing sahara module from upstream,
which is not contain such actions.

Partial implements: blueprint upgrade-openstack-puppet-modules

So this change looks ok, but I question if this is something that falls under the upgrade openstack modules blueprint. Additionally bug 1462050 which was created out of the discussions of bug 1461400, was created with the goal of switching to hourly rotations rather than the every 10/30 minutes we have today.  If the end goal is to move to a simpler rotation schedule but on an hourly basis, we might still want to leverage the anacron class which basically wedges in an hourly schedule.  Thoughts?'}, {'account_id': 13948, 'date': '2015-06-17 06:13:41.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

There is nothing useful about anacron class. The only thing it does is overwriting upstream provided files with at best shady replacements. I don't see how could it be utilized for incoming logrotate reorganization – it's just bunch of conditionals that can be easily bring back to openstack::logrotate if needed.

About how it fits related blueprint, I've talked to Sergii and we decided to include it as other modules (qpid, puppetmaster, epel) are also removed there."}, {'account_id': 13343, 'date': '2015-06-17 09:52:34.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 14985, 'date': '2015-06-17 13:37:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

commit_message:
Move anacron module functionality to openstack::logrotate

The sole purpose of this module was replacing anacron-related files
provided by upstream packages and enabling more frequent logs rotation
schedule.

Change-Id: Ib839a3d7fcf6182e9d9d6149dd4c2ed727371c81
Implements: blueprint upgrade-openstack-puppet-modules

commit_message:
Bind novncproxy to its own network

By default the nova vncproxy binds to 0.0.0.0, which will fail in
a loadbalanced environment.  This makes it bind to its network.

Change-Id: I08776a8f6c72b63d73433b147c130fbc9a7110b0

From my further investigation, using launcher.stop instead of raise SignalExit breaks cinder-volume graceful shutdown. When I apply your patch to Cinder and send SIGTERM to parent process of cinder-volume, all processes are forcibly stopped instantly.

Here are steps for reproducing.

0) Add rpcserver.wait() into stop method in Service class of cinder/service.py like this.

    def stop(self):
    ...
        try:
            self.rpcserver.stop()
            self.rpcserver.wait()
        except Exception:

1) create cinder environment using devstack. Make sure the cinder backend does not have "volume_clear = none" config option in ciner.conf backend section.(This option skips volume initialization. Since this step will send SIGTERM during this initialization, we disable this option)

3) Delete the volume & Run kill -SIGTERM <PID> for parent cinder-volume process during volume deletion.

commit_message:
Revert "service child process normal SIGTERM exit"

After introducing commit Ie51669bd278288b768311ddf56ad31a2f28cc7ab,
child processes which are launched via ProcessLauncher are always
killed forcibly when they catch SIGTERM from parents. This breaks
existing graceful shutdown mechanism and kills child processes
even if they are ongoing.

This patch reverts the above commit and recovers functionality of
graceful shutdown again.

Change-Id: I50f57a605edf226b0c4e93234930df9c37209474
Closes-bug: 1463132

commit_message:
Add tests for python-cinderclient and style fix

Add test for cinder extra-specs-list command output.
Add test for cinder list-extension command output.
Fix pep8 issues "E128 continuation line under-indented for visual
indent" in other functions.

Change-Id: I28266af7a6ff23b83899c50cc230f926a44592dc
Partial-Bug: #1463404

commit_message:
Update version for Liberty

Update the version for Liberty, switching from date-based versioning
to pre-versioning using SemVer. See
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-May/065211.html
and
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-June/067082.html
for details.

Change-Id: I6a35fa0dda798fad93b804d00a46af80f08d475c

commit_message:
Fix dependencies for stable/juno branch

We have several incompatibilities for stable/juno branch that should be fixed:

1) Update of global requirements
- All updates are done using "update.py" module of requirements project:
- python update.py ../manila

2) Bump stable/juno version to 2014.2.1 to fix pbr incompatibility

3) Make Tempest use stable version
- cherry-picked I5760461c1ebf8cf53ccfae55606fe6036c915e02 and used appropriate
commit/state of Tempest, that is different than used one in cherry-pick commit.

These fixes should have been done separately, but now, this is the only way to
fix gates for stable/juno - all three at once.

Change-Id: I775ddb54cb2c75cc7f331d7ab6c98ecfcfa7b5e4

To address some bugs about large amount of disks,
huge disks, etc. we introduced workarounds in
nailgun data driver in fuel agent.

The issue is that when only one disk on a node,
nailgun places /boot not on raid but on plain parition
and flag boot_done is set only inside 'if raid' clause,
but not inside 'if partition' clause.

Closes-Bug: #1465971
"}]
commit_message:
IBP: Fixed provision fail on a node with one disk

To address some bugs about large amount of disks,
huge disks, etc. we introduced workarounds in
nailgun data driver in fuel agent.

The issue is that when only one disk on a node,
nailgun places /boot not on raid but on plain parition
and flag boot_done is set only inside 'if raid' clause,
but not inside 'if partition' clause.

Change-Id: I8a598ccde661fae375bb102f36550fb53f1abbe8
Closes-Bug: #1465971

commit_message:
Fix default auth credentials in freezer-api.conf

The default credentials in freezer-api.conf
erroneously used the admin user and tenant

Now they contain the user "freezer" and tenant "service".

This is consistent with the installation documentation

Closes bug: #1465712

Change-Id: Icd315c2613980fac41c958b5854a2a10c5a8c6c2

commit_message:
Add specification for vswitch::ovs on FreeBSD

Specified the default expected parameters for vswitch::ovs when
used under FreeBSD. Also, some minor changes were made to the
vswitch::ovs parameters, most notably the addition of a status
parameter for the required services (ovs-vswitchd,ovsdb-server).

Change-Id: Id61eb3afe70b1c96a0131a629a9993e860868489

Fix warning for duplicated links

it's name.
See: http://docutils.sourceforge.net/docs/ref/rst/restructuredtext.html#anonymous-hyperlinks

commit_message:
Experimental upgrade of environment 5.1.1 to 6.0

Add chapter to Operations document with description of procedure that upgrades
Mirantis OpenStack environment 5.1.1 to 6.0 for limited set of Reference
Architecture options.

Change-Id: I8794cee8c0ea94b6691fd5184ba84c4e7cf5ca7e
Closes-Bug: 1455032
Implements: blueprint upgrade-major-openstack-environment

commit_message:
Parameter can not be test in Huawei driver

In test_huawei_nas.py:
The 'Call' function of the parameters('data') can not be
test. Because of the variable('data') is assigned None in line 93.
So modify the variable name from 'data' to 'result'.

Change-Id: I96249e5c2e5ca59a9dad754deb29c7c0530e9caf
Closes-Bug: #1465507

commit_message:
Move interface wait time to netconfig task

For a workaround for bug 1458625, a 32 second sleep was added to the
url_available function that is run as part of the connectivity_tests
task that is run after netconfig. This wait should be part of the
netconfig task where the delay is needed when bringing up a new
bridge in ubuntu.  This will help ensure that the interfaces are ready
after the netconfig task if the url_available task is removed or
tasks are run in a different order.

Change-Id: Ie715d6bf1622d33dd10b15c5bea74e05f1bba858
Related-Bug: 1458625
Closes-Bug: 1458954

commit_message:
IBP: add GRUB_RECORDFAIL_TIMEOUT for ubuntu

This timeout hasn't been set in default grub2 config.
If a provisioned node experiences unexpected reboot,
grub will refuse to boot after it and will expect for
user input for confirmation.

Setting it to 5secs should help to bypass that confirmation.

This change additionaly allow to set GRUB timeout via config file.

Change-Id: I48af989bc8ad4ccaf2939804614488588010fed2
Closes-Bug: #1465586

commit_message:
IBP: Fixed provision fail on a node with one disk

To address some bugs about large amount of disks,
huge disks, etc. we introduced workarounds in
nailgun data driver in fuel agent.

The issue is that when only one disk on a node,
nailgun places /boot not on raid but on plain parition
and flag boot_done is set only inside 'if raid' clause,
but not inside 'if partition' clause.

Change-Id: I8a598ccde661fae375bb102f36550fb53f1abbe8
Closes-Bug: #1465971

commit_message:
Fix when logic for boolean handling

Turns out Ansible has a specific way for booleans to be handled
correctly, so we no longer need to attempt a boolean compare and
a string compare.

Changes the use_cirros logic so a user can disable that logic path.

Change-Id: I49dcdb66f8c65f3fa13f3270ee610ab9e44eeacc
Closes-Bug: 1465408

commit_message:
Missing template file on update fails silently

When the template file for a template/facade/provider resource is
not found in the new files list when doing a stack update, Heat
silently falls back to using the existing template (i.e. so no
change will be made).
The cause is that the update code shares the same code path for
obtaining the template as the init code. The init code needs to
have a fallback, so that loading the (parent) stack never fails,
however in the update case it is undesirable.

Change-Id: Id12b63d9f04caba8e9325aed0ee2acf51ffe0c4c
Closes-Bug: #1452520

commit_message:
Use correct property name in get_details of os.nova.server profile

'created' and 'updated' properties of nova server resource were
renamed to 'created_at' and 'updated_at' in recent patch of
openstacksdk. Therefore this patch revised do_get_details method of
os.nova.server profile to use the correct property name. It also
added 'progress' property which could be used in future.

Change-Id: I45ffef152e3ebdb3e656ae452a67b3f6242e1e9a

commit_message:
Enable horizon integration tests voting

There was some failures in tests itself that lead to wrong 'verified'
votes for correct patches.
After depending patch would be merged (last fix), gate job would be
reliable again.

Depends-On: Ic927723d10bc45d3ec862c4f7d3152890114e39e
Change-Id: I0de5754ad686aeea8946f418d381d7e16cf81e42

enviroment when stack restore.

commit_message:
Make image-create require data or at least one argument

Creating image without data and arguments is a silly operation, most
likely a result of user expecting `glance image-create` to print help.

In case it is desired, new '--blank' argument can be used.

Fixes bug #1184965

Change-Id: I3b763a5e78c821d57da090126b1261eccbed3379

commit_message:
Make image-create require data or at least one argument

Creating image without data and arguments is a silly operation, most
likely a result of user expecting `glance image-create` to print help.

In case it is desired, new '--blank' argument can be used.

Closes-Bug: #1184965

Change-Id: Id4e78cb898a71263c7839a36f81425c8352134a8

commit_message:
Use `inferred=True` by default

Rabbitmq's amqp1.0 plugin doesn't have support for vbin8, which is the
default encoding used by qpid-proton. In order to workaround this issue
we should use inferred=True.

Closes-bug: #1465409
Change-Id: Id265917244d7e152c5e13a10df367a3e59de8e50
(cherry picked from commit c8845b4bef4248fad4a9da8dad0455495b2bc6fd)

commit_message:
Fix live migration

Move the compute pool creation from controller to compute role due to it was
so initially and compute role needs to have ceph keys to work correctly.

Change-Id: Ieb011dae49aec07dd239a23f97400bff786023c2
Closes-bug: #1466075

commit_message:
Make heatclient-dsvm-functional gating for heatcli

All related patches were merged and check job is green, so
heatclient-dsvm-functional job may be used as gating voting job now.

Change-Id: I82076f1053e9b14fdc7c59fa88231cf48a891476

commit_message:
Document image-based provisioning and Fuel Agent

Added ref-arch/9000-fuel-provision.rst to explain how IBP works.

Added terminology articles: image-based provisioning and Fuel Agent

Added section to user-guide/settings for the screen where
image-based provisioning is selected.

Updated the Release Notes "new feature" note to point to these
other docs and remove the link to the blueprint.

We need a file-ref page for fuel-agent.config; this will be done
in a separate commit and then this doc will reference that.

Change-Id: Ibe674a1d7fca6cce447ac2e62b91bf1bac56cc37

commit_message:
Fix for miratis doc templates.

To make fuel-qa docs suitable as a
documentation it has to be in
Mirantis style.

commit_message:
logging failed exception info for add image operation

Add image operation failed will lead to rollback operation,
delete this image if it was created.
If this operation throws some exception, previous one will be
overwritten so that we cannot elegantly trace the problem occurs.
We recommend logging failed exception info before rollback operation.

Change-Id: I403fcf7be13d2d01b2da8cd9d5e06ac355a47b25
modified:   glance_store/_drivers/rbd.py

Listing policies filtered by service endpoint URL

This change specify the ``endpoint_url`` filter
for listing policies. It allows the filtering by
an encoded service endpoint URL.

commit_message:
Graceful shutdown of API server

Currently, killing a API server will immediately stop WSGI service which
interrupts in-process request. This will cause problem when do upgrading.
This patch gracefuly handle shutdown.

This patch should not be merged. It is just a proof of concept for review
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/190175/

Change-Id: I5d0b094108748e0d5507dfed006173745d1f4128

commit_message:
Switched Heat engine to ResourceGroup use

Sahara now uses two layers of ResourceGroups:
1. Each node group is represented as ResourceGroup with specified
   count.
2. Volumes for the instance are also represented as ResourceGroup
   with a specified count.

Note: Heat creates two nested stacks for ResourceGroup (one for
nested group, other to support multiple copies). This means that
'max_nested_stack_depth' config in Heat must be at least 4.

Also, there is no sense in checking exact structure of resulting
Heat templates. But there is a sense in checking specific methods.
So, deleted all template tests and added test for security_groups.

Implements blueprint: heat-template-decomposition

Change-Id: I1bc1ea31344a2e4d624bbf2836aa51897453efe2

commit_message:
Fix migration to allow various mysql engines

MySQL/MariaDB databases allow running various db engines with default
InnoDB. neutron-db-manage allows specification of mysql engine though
setting different engine via config file or flag --mysql-engine
does not work because a few places still have 'InnoDB' hard-coded.

Change-Id: If858d29a372f80859139d2cf8599df7a199cb5c2
Closes-Bug: #1464291

commit_message:
Basic support for API versions

Currently only one version (1, 0) is supported, and no header is
send to the server. However, this change allows calling code to
fix version (1, 0) already.

Change-Id: I1636e39d5a4c4344bd3e159d559886607d0c285e
Closes-Bug: #1465359

commit_message:
Ensure no "db" related functional/fullstack tests are skipped in the gate

Currently neutron uses MySQLTestCase[1] and
PostgreSQLOpportunisticTestCase[2] for functional and fullstack tests
using a real MySQL/PostgreSQL database. These classes skip tests when
the db is unavailable (db not installed/configured, missing packages,
etc.) which is fine when tests are runned by developers but not when
runned by the gate jobs.

This change updates MySQLTestCase[1] and defines PostgreSQLTestCase[1]
as PostgreSQL oslo.db test class wrapper: when the db is unavailable,
these classes ensure tests will:

* fail in the gate (dsvm-functional, dsvm-fullstack jobs),
* be skipped by default otherwise (functional, fullstack jobs).

[1] neutron.tests.common.base
[2] oslo_db.sqlalchemy.test_base

Closes-Bug: #1404093
Change-Id: I77b12e728ce9a7b0222c3df081842635f6375a3e

[{'created': '2015-05-28 19:08:35.000000000', 'message': 'WIP: Graceful shutdown WSGI server

Currently, killing a nova-api will immediately stop WSGI service which
interrupts in-process request. This will cause problem when do upgrading.
The patch do two thing:
On master process side, stopping server (close socket) before sends
KILL signal to children process. Because if master still open the socket,
user can successfully connects to API server but gets no response.
On children process side, closing socket first, then waits for all greenlets
to finish, finally exits it self.
DocImpact: graceful termination of process is not instantaneous.
To force instantaneous termination second SIGTERM signal must be sent.

Change-Id: If25f9565d832d1c36642ec3b1921563ef02890aa
Closes-bug: #1382390
Co-Author: Tiantian Gao <gtt116@gmail.com>

'}, {'created': '2015-06-04 13:41:48.000000000', 'message': "Graceful shutdown WSGI server

Currently, termination of WSGI application immediately stops service and so
interrupts in-progress request. This could cause problem when do upgrading.

Following related things were done:
1. Removed signal handler for SIGINT to allow instantaneous shutdown.
2. Call launcher.stop() was moved from _child_wait_for_exit_or_signal method
to SIGTERM signal handler and pipe_watcher method because service must not be
stopped for example if SIGHUP comes.
3. Added stop server operation before sending TERM signal to children
processes to close listening socket in master process. Because if socket in
master process is opened, user could successfully connects to API server but
without receiving response.
4. On children side before calling _exit() added call launcher.wait() to allow
gracefully shutdown on SIGTERM.
5. Removed service.wait() from Services.stop() to make it not-blocking call.
6. Removed stop-start operations from Services.restart method because of two
reasons:
  - why stop/start service if we have reset() service's method;
  - to allow graceful shutdown implementation of service.stop() must contain
    closing listening server socket. And there is no possibility to open new
    socket and bind it with current address/port in service.start method if it
    was closed.

DocImpact: graceful termination of process can be done by sending SIGTERM
signal to parent WSGI process. Graceful termination is not instantaneous.
To force instantaneous termination SIGINT signal must be sent.

Closes-bug: #1382390
Co-Author: Tiantian Gao <gtt116@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Graceful shutdown WSGI server

Currently, termination of WSGI application immediately stops service and so
interrupts in-progress request. This could cause problem when do upgrading.

Following related things were done:
1. Removed signal handler for SIGINT to allow instantaneous shutdown.
2. Call launcher.stop() was moved from _child_wait_for_exit_or_signal method
to SIGTERM signal handler and pipe_watcher method because service must not be
stopped for example if SIGHUP comes.
3. Added stop server operation before sending TERM signal to children
processes to close listening socket in master process. Because if socket in
master process is opened, user could successfully connects to API server but
without receiving response.
4. On children side before calling _exit() added call launcher.wait() to allow
gracefully shutdown on SIGTERM.
5. Removed service.wait() from Services.stop() to make it not-blocking call.
6. Removed stop-start operations from Services.restart method because of two
reasons:
  - why stop/start service if we have reset() service's method;
  - to allow graceful shutdown implementation of service.stop() must contain
    closing listening server socket. And there is no possibility to open new
    socket and bind it with current address/port in service.start method if it
    was closed.

DocImpact: graceful termination of process can be done by sending SIGTERM
signal to parent WSGI process. Graceful termination is not instantaneous.
To force instantaneous termination SIGINT signal must be sent.

Change-Id: If25f9565d832d1c36642ec3b1921563ef02890aa
Closes-bug: #1382390
Co-Author: Tiantian Gao <gtt116@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Update version for Liberty

Update the version for Liberty, switching from date-based versioning
to pre-versioning using SemVer. See
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-May/065211.html
and
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-June/067082.html
for details.

Change-Id: I6a35fa0dda798fad93b804d00a46af80f08d475c

commit_message:
Graceful shutdown of RPC server

Currently, killing a RPC server will immediately stop service which
interrupts in-process request.
This patch gracefuly handle shutdown.

This patch should not be merged. It is just a proof of concept for review
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/190175/

Change-Id: I12dafb35850045a0b01b0be3a8b7c85508b540ae

@Adrian, yes, I think the bay locks are advisory in nature in term of returning a status instead of throwing an exception. Conductors will acquire locks. If a bay is locked, that means it is in a transitional states (being created/updated/deleted), and it should reject any other request until the current operation finishes (Later, we would consider to give exception to the delete operation. That means delete operation can interrupt current operation).

Read operations (list/get) is not performed by conductors so these operations can be performed concurrently. Write operations (create/update/delete) will be perform exclusively on the same bay.'}, {'account_id': 11536, 'date': '2015-04-11 16:27:22.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 4.'}, {'account_id': 11536, 'date': '2015-04-11 16:35:05.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

[{'created': '2015-04-09 04:41:37.000000000', 'message': '[WIP] Support multiple conductors for scaling

Since conductors will be more than one, we need to lock the bay
that performs an atomic operation. Requests will be deliver to
conductors in a round-robin way. If a conductor locked a bay and crashes,
another conductor will try to steal the locks to move forward.

Change-Id: I95f28361eea361d878d2c047937c3beef4fb445a
Implements: blueprint horizontal-scale
'}, {'created': '2015-04-10 23:38:45.000000000', 'message': 'Database changes for horizontal-scale support

Add database APIs for a conductor to lock or release a bay.
In addition, add an API for a conductor to steal the
lock of a bay that was locked by another conductor.

Change-Id: I95f28361eea361d878d2c047937c3beef4fb445a
Partial-Implements: blueprint horizontal-scale
'}, {'created': '2015-04-11 16:09:01.000000000', 'message': 'Database changes for conductor horizontal scale

Add database APIs for a conductor to lock/steal/release a bay.
There will be more than one conductors, so it is necessary to
implement a distributed locking APIs to prevent race condictions.

* Lock acquisition: A conductor should acquire a lock when it is
  about to perform an operation on a bay (e.g. create/update/delete
  a bay). The conductor should check the return value of the APIs
  to determine if the lock is successfully acquired. If yes, another
  conductor that attempts to lock the same bay will not succeed.
  Upon completion, the conductor should release the acquired lock to
  allow other conductors to operate the bay later.
* Lock stealing: If conductor A acquires a lock and crashes
  unexpectedly, conductor B can steal the lock acquired by
  conductor A. To do that, conductor B needs to give the id of
  conductor A along with other parameters. The lock stealing will
  succeed if the bay is indeed locked by conductor A at the moment
  of the stealing requests.

Change-Id: I95f28361eea361d878d2c047937c3beef4fb445a

commit_message:
Database changes for conductor horizontal scale

Add database APIs for a conductor to lock/steal/release a bay.
There will be more than one conductors, so it is necessary to
implement a distributed locking APIs to prevent race conditions.

* Lock acquisition: A conductor should acquire a lock when it is
  about to perform an operation on a bay (e.g. create/update/delete
  a bay). The conductor should check the return value of the APIs
  to determine if the lock is successfully acquired. If yes, another
  conductor that attempts to lock the same bay will not succeed.
  Upon completion, the conductor should release the acquired lock to
  allow other conductors to operate the bay later.
* Lock stealing: If conductor A acquires a lock and crashes
  unexpectedly, conductor B can steal the lock acquired by
  conductor A. To do that, conductor B needs to give the id of
  conductor A along with other parameters. The lock stealing will
  succeed if the bay is indeed locked by conductor A at the moment
  of the stealing requests.

Change-Id: I95f28361eea361d878d2c047937c3beef4fb445a
Partial-Implements: blueprint horizontal-scale

commit_message:
Use ebtables to isolate dhcp traffic

Iptables doesn't properly block the broadcast traffic crossing
the bridge, so use ebtables instead. Removes test which is no
longer valid since we are not using iptables anymore.

Conflicts:
        nova/tests/network/test_linux_net.py

Change-Id: I43e5f1fe9512dd3ec9595c7203bc46837cef3cad
Closes-Bug: #1318104
(cherry picked from commit 1236b09076cca3b4b16538b055e52edde5a4feea)

commit_message:
Rework nova_v2 driver

Some erroneous implementations were included into nova_v2 driver
when switching sdk interface from resource call to function call.
This patch fixed these errors to make nova_v2 driver work.

Change-Id: Idabdf2c062d52ff6a0627328fa10d6255cf9bcaa

commit_message:
Delay interpolating the LOG string

If the log level isn't even enabled, we can avoid interpolating
the formatted string completly, so choose to do that by default.

Change-Id: Ibf2253b859a9196a0f4cebd78b565fedf5199832

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks

    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. Also it
    takes generally at least a couple of weeks for cores to get around to
    reviewing code. The more you participate in the community the more

    eventually approved. Get to know others and become known by doing code
    reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a great way to learn the code base.

commit_message:
Add missing backups entry to default quota class

Default quota class stores default setting for quota, however,
backup quota is missing into the database. As result deprecated
message caused: "Deprecated: Default quota for resource:<resource>
is set by the default quota flag: <quota flag>, it is now
deprecated. Please use the default quota class for default quota."

This commit add default entry for quota at migration time if there
is not already in 'default' quota class.

Change-Id: Iba9af1ec1aee72841682c6ea1a9cfe6d2a2078ef
Partial-Bug: #1435807

commit_message:
Allow customization of dhcp_domain setting from agents/dhcp.pp

With this patch we aim at making the dhcp_domain setting
customizable from the agents/dhcp class.

Change-Id: I457ae90cb8de500998e9d4775f2832747d052628

script so that building uses correct tags.

commit_message:
Add Neutron Loadbalancer v1 create and update pools

Enable benchmarking of the Neutron LoadBalancer v1
lb-pool-create and lb-pool-update APIs. Due to the
different API scheme and confusing naming conventions
in Neutron (LB is v1 API and LBaaS for v2 API) the
appropriate code is explicitly marked with 'v1'
since this only implements the API v1 benchmarking.

Change-Id: I15c9c8878391ba30ec7da6fa91231e8fed1d23cf

[{'created': '2015-06-18 08:37:34.000000000', 'message': 'Set max volume size limit for the tenant

There is a need to limit maximum size of a volume to levels
that the storage infrastructure can handle.
Setting a maximum limit on size of a volume also prevents
a tenant from creating large volumes that have not been tested
and certified to satisfy SLA objectives.

This feature allows admin to set volume size limit
[per_volume_gigabytes] for a tenant.

Change-Id: I407f09f442934220394466a8aca9331534fb6df5
Implements: blueprint cinder-quota-define-per-volume
'}]
commit_message:
Set max volume size limit for the tenant

There is a need to limit maximum size of a volume to levels
that the storage infrastructure can handle.
Setting a maximum limit on size of a volume also prevents
a tenant from creating large volumes that have not been tested
and certified to satisfy SLA objectives.

This feature allows admin to set volume size limit
[per_volume_gigabytes] for a tenant.

Change-Id: I407f09f442934220394466a8aca9331534fb6df5
Implements: blueprint cinder-quota-define-per-volume

commit_message:
Devstack to support an IPv6 infra installation

Currently devstack provides the necessary support to have an IPv4 based
OpenStack infrastructure where the services are binded to IPv4 addresses.
However, it does not support an IPv6 infra installation where OpenStack
services are binded to IPv6 addresses.

While testing such a setup, it is observed that some of the parameters
are not configurable/set by devstack. Because of this, the respective
openstack components would use the default values for some parameters
(which generally fall-back to using the IPv4 address of the host).

This patch would help us in configuring the required parameters, to achieve
an IPv6 based OpenStack setup.

Closes-Bug: #1447692
Change-Id: If13e60ee879395e07f26c0094b1b4c0dd481bd51

[{'created': '2015-06-10 06:34:32.000000000', 'message': "Stack updated error if creation fails

commit_message:
Stack updated error if creation fails

template https://github.com/openstack/heat-templates/blob/
67301b6ff45b9f1c220ee0a0ab3aecd3a415032b/cfn/F17/
AutoScalingCeilometer.yaml
can have update error when execute on some resources
which did not even created due to creation failed.

Add check logic in _needs_update to make sure even resource still
stay in init complete state can proceed update process by
raise resource.UpdateReplace.

For nested stack, StackResource should have the same status check
logic in _needs_update method to avoid this error occur(nested()
is None due to resource in failed state after create failed).

Change-Id: I3fa6a61436e79409fe7f28cf66dfdfd9f609b576
Closes-Bug: #1459719

commit_message:
use announce list instead of dev list

Change the default email_to address to the openstack-announce mailing
list instead of openstack-dev.

Add an --email-reply-to option to control where replies should go, and
set the default to the openstack-dev mailing list.

Change-Id: Ia22d0f2a01c6c55a72ddc0f8eb97cbb501c8af70

commit_message:
let the caller specify the project owner

If the repository hasn't been added to the governance repo yet, the tool
to figure out which project tag to add will fail. Let the user specify
the value as an environment variable.

Change-Id: Ibc06c330c3a179fd5b128ce6952fae577729d7d9
